The course will explore Roman epic poetry. The student will analyse
Roman epic texts and acquire knowledge of the history, composition, versification, language and style of Roman epic.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide knowledge about the history and development of Roman epic, its main authors, their style, syntax, verse technique and vocabulary. The students will learn to analyse different textual levels and to use special dictionaries, textual commentaries and critical apparatus.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The course will develop the competence in philological analysis of texts, the ability to comprehend the morphological and syntactical structure of Latin texts, the faculty to use special dictionaries, textual commentaries and critical apparatus.
